default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default6.1.
default 
defaultThe statutory functions of the LA must be made known to all sponsors by the DFE. These functions must be fully supported in all academies for example, care order requirements, child protection, place planning, excluded pupils, SEND requirements, Educationa
defaultl Psychology support, FSM, attendance. 
default&#xa0;
default6.2.
default 
defaultAs long as the process is transparent and academies and academy chains are not excluded then there is no reason that LAs cannot continue to hold the role of place planning; the decision making needs to be conducted 
defaulton behalf of all children not select groups of vocal families
default&#xa0;
default6.3.
default 
defaultA duty to collaborate for all sponsors including free schools should be an implicit part of the funding agreement.
default&#xa0;
default6.4.
default 
defaultThe development of an escalation route that stops short of whistle-blowing to
default enable academies and academy groups to work with LAs on child protection is needed urgently.
default&#xa0;
default6.5.
default 
defaultIt is important for schools to be sponsored in ways that do not simply replicate the role of LAs, bringing little gain for the academies or their pupils. Academy
default sponsorship should bring rigorous governance and greater independence and autonomy within a democratic process. 
default&#xa0;
default6.6.
default 
defaultGovernance in academies enables removal of ineffective governors and more rapid intervention to raise standards. 
default&#xa0;
